annotation.TEXT: To be continued... :P
GAH! How did I not see this typo until now?! This should obviously say "obviously", not "obviouslt"!
Power up! I think that'll do. I'm not going to spend the time to hit the other block.
Oh, man. Upwards bullets. But that's a good thing here.
Whoa! That's alright, since I was gonna Start+Select out anyway!
Thank you, shell, for allowing me to clobber that Hammer Brother, and I think I'll use it on these piranha plants, too.
Huh, there's a key and keyhole. I wonder if that pipe I saw just before the goal that I obviously needed a P-switch to reach would take me right there...
Okay, now since I can't jump, I'll have to use this note block back here in order to stomp this P-switch.
Yes, dodged that evil saw that took away my fire flower last time.

That reveals the path leading to :). But, before I end the video, I want to try to reach that goal near the beginning of NOJUNP NOLIFE, even though it's totally unnecessary. I wonder if bringing a Yoshi will help me...
Umm... As I was saying before I bashed my head into that parakoopa's feet, how do I reach this goal?
Okay, I didn't get hammered there this time...
D'oh. I shouldn't have clunked those two shells together. Now I can't take out this Hammer Guy.
Oh, man. Saws. What is this place, some sort of logging industry that raocow had Mario fight against over five years ago?
Whoa, close shave there. I think Mario wants to keep his mustache intact.
Push!

Umm... I have a feeling that my cape will screw me over with the bullet bounce here, so I'm going to intentionally lose it. (I wish I hadn't lost my fire flower earlier, because I could've just switched to that if I still had it.)
So, yeah. You have to deal with enemies and stuff without being able to jump. Fortunately, I have power ups leftover from the previous level that'll help me out.
D'oh, right. This is a "No Yoshi" level.
Huh. Seems like the bullets disappear the instant they touch the top of the screen.
Oww...
Nuts. It looks like I'm one duder short. (Looking back, if I hadn't grabbed the shell after KO-ing the first Hammer Bro., I could've gotten a 1-up from this combo.)
Well, then how...
Well, I'm not going to try to figure it out now, since I'm low on time. However, I believe this level has two exits, so maybe I'll figure it out on my second visit to this level.
Oh, man. We gotta do bullet bouncing here.

If you saw some weird graphics during the black screen there, I blame ZSNES, as that's exactly where I ended one movie file and started recording on another movie file (to reduce desync risk and lost progress if a desync does occur). Alright, that opened up a path to I Can't Go Back Anymore. Now to reenter NOJUNP NOLIFE and figure out how to reach the secret exit.
However, this time, I have no power ups to help me out here, so this might be a bit more interesting...
Hey there duders, and welcome back to Super Mario Raspberry Raspberry Raspberry, or Phbbbbt Phbbbbt Phbbbbt for short! Alright let's take a look at the voting results here...
Aww! Why do you taunt me with all those unreachable coins?!

Now, some of you might've been screaming at the screen that I wasted the P-switch here last time. And yeah, I totally don't need to use the P-switch to cross these single-tile gaps. Just run across while holding a jump button.
Oh, and there were late votes for IT'S OVER 9000, :D, and NOJUNP NOLIFE, which were made after I had already put this video together, so NOJUNP NOLIFE actually got 17 total votes.
I forget the exact details, but that picture appeared on SMW Central a couple years ago I think during something involving "System" or whatever.
Ooh, needed a bullet from back there to reach these parakoopas. (Well, with my cape, I suppose I didn't actually need the bullet.)
Zwee!
No Yoshis allowed because they horse around too much.
Still no problem even without a cape.

Any idea what this moonspeak says? (I would guess that it's probably just simply saying something like "Mario cannot jump in this level".) (UPDATE: Biospark88 says that it is basically that. It says "Unable to jump".

However, even though straight up jumping doesn't work, the jump buttons still very slightly slow your falling speed (or let you glide with a cape), and still allow you to control how high you go when you bounce off of an enemy or note block, like usual.
Even without any power ups, I can still kill these duders by using this shell, which is nice.
Gotta check every pipe...
Oh, man. Podoboos coming out of lava... Or maybe that's orange soda. Doesn't matter, since I can't even reach that liquid down there.
Can I avoid getting my head shaved this time?
Alright, that's enough comboing. I don't have all day. Now I have to deal with downward bullets.
Yeah, I can totally use this shell to hit those ! blocks.
I hope I don't get fried by these Stop & Shop Guaranteed Value Orange Soda Podoboos.
Goal tape average so far: 70 / 3 = 23.333 stars each.
Ooh, there's the goal! However, since I can't jump, I can't reach it. This shell I've got can reach it, but having the shell pass through the goal doesn't do anything special.
I Can't Go Back Anymore
Oh, with the help of my cape, I can totally 1-up combo these things!
Hmm... I have a feeling that I'm supposed to place a springboard there eventually.
So, which of these remaining levels should I play next? There are four to pick from, so place your votes now!
Yep, there's the goal. There's no way I was gonna get any decent number of bonus stars there, but maybe I should've tried for the few I could've gotten. Oh, well.
So, yeah. As you can see, in this level, any attempts to jump will prove futile. (That brief rapid spinning I did there was caused by me hitting the turbo A button.)
Whoa! I got lucky there!
BGM: Contra Hard Corps - Simon 1994RD
Ack! I hate the unforgiving hitboxes of upside-down saws!
Alright, so NOJUNP NOLIFE it is!
BGM: Seiken Densetsu 3 - Powell
You know, there's no reason that I absolutely must drop the springboard right in that hole on the springboard shadow there.
It so looked like that lower saw passed through Mario's feet there, but the upright saws are more forgiving with their hitboxes.
Ow! That was me being impatient.
The cape made that one a bit easier.
Here I was hoping I'd encounter just one more guy to clobber with this shell, but unfortunately, there aren't any before I have to deal with this next puzzle.
Clonk! Well, I ended up getting hammered there...
Alright, I'll leave the P-switch there for the moment while I backtrack with the springboard.
Oh, geez. I've been spending too much time doing things like comboing with the cape earlier.
Vanilla Secret Yu
Hi, Yoshi!
There we go, and there's the springboard that I was expecting to find, and there's a locked door. So, I guess I'm gonna be backtracking with the springboard.
Ah! So that's how I get that Yoshi coin. I wasn't able to last time because I had killed that parakoopa beforehand.
Okay, so I've got the key I need to open that door, and I just barely avoided getting hammered there...
Ha! I ducked that hammer this time!
I like how those note blocks can kill the downwards bullets there.
Yeah, not quite enough for a 1-up combo there. However, if that paragoomba was here as well, I certainly could've reached the 1-up mark.
Now, let's get me my mushroom back...
Click! Door's open, and I hope the goal is just up ahead...
Nope, not that I can see. Alright, so there's the secret exit!
Looks like activating the Yellow Switch Palace has some use here.
Ooh, can I get a 1-up combo?
Alright. They're all taken care of. Too bad I couldn't get any big combos going without a cape. Oh, well.
Hmm... I probably should've grabbed that parakoopa's shell to use against this paragoomba, but whatever. I can still dodge this guy no problem.
This means that I can save this P-switch for later, and I know exactly where I want to use it. (And you guys probably know exactly where I want to use it as well.)
Whoops. I kind of want that Yoshi coin.
Click!
Alright, I'll certainly take that power up.
:P :P :P
Maybe it is actually unreachable, but if there is a way to reach it, let me know!
That was kind of tricky, and would've been way trickier without the yellow ! blocks. Hmm... I wonder if I can get any mushrooms from them...
Umm... I wonder how I'm supposed to reach that last Yoshi coin...
And, there you go! But, before I put the key in the keyhole, is there anything to the right?
Monster combo! (10 hits) 3-life combo!
